== 秘密追蹤 ==
從2011年4月20日，傳媒廣泛談論iPhone和其他iOS裝置中的一個隱藏已[[加密|加密]]的檔案<ref>{{Cite web |title=Consolidated.db: Final Thoughts |url=http://blog.csvance.com/?p=136 |accessdate=2011-04-25 |author=Christopher Vance |date=2011-04-20 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110424034023/http://blog.csvance.com/?p=136 |archivedate=2011-04-24 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref name="Wired1">{{Cite news |url=http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2011/04/iphone-tracks |title=iPhone Tracks Your Every Move, and There's a Map for That |author=Chen, Brian X. |date=2011-04-20 |work=Wired |accessdate=2011-04-22 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110424072530/http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2011/04/iphone-tracks |archivedate=2011-04-24 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。據稱該檔案標示著“consolidated.db”，會不斷儲存由手機訊號塔發出的用戶移動位置定位，但此技術被證明有時候是不準確的<ref name="O">{{Cite web |title=Additional iPhone tracking research |url=http://radar.oreilly.com/2011/04/more-iphone-tracking-research.html |accessdate=2011-04-25 |author=Warden, Pete |date=2011-04-24 |publisher=[[O'Reilly_Media|O'Reilly Media]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110426071601/http://radar.oreilly.com/2011/04/more-iphone-tracking-research.html |archivedate=2011-04-26 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。此檔案是在2010年6月與蘋果公司更新的iOS 4一同發布，並可能載有接近一年的數據價值。以往版本的iOS儲存類似的訊息於一個稱為"h-cells.plist"的檔案中<ref>{{Cite web |title=3 Major Issues with the Latest iPhone Tracking "Discovery" |url=http://alexlevinson.wordpress.com/2011/04/21/3-major-issues-with-the-latest-iphone-tracking-discovery |accessdate=2011-04-25 |author=Alex Levinson |date=2011-04-21 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110424111624/http://alexlevinson.wordpress.com/2011/04/21/3-major-issues-with-the-latest-iphone-tracking-discovery/ |archivedate=2011-04-24 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

[[F-Secure|F-Secure公司]]發現一天兩次把數據傳送到蘋果公司，推測蘋果公司正利用這些資料來建構他們的全球定位數據庫，類似於通過[[戰爭駕駛|戰爭駕駛]]來建構的[[Google|谷歌]]和{{link-en|Skyhook Wireless|Skyhook Wireless}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=Actually, iPhone sends your location to Apple twice a day |url=http://www.f-secure.com/weblog/archives/00002145.html |accessdate=2011-04-25 |author=Mikko Hypponen |date=2011-04-21 |authorlink=Mikko Hypponen |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110424111810/http://www.f-secure.com/weblog/archives/00002145.html |archivedate=2011-04-24 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。然而，不像[[Google|谷歌]]的應用程式"Latitude"，它執行類似[[Android|Android]]手機的任務，此檔案是不依賴一個特定的[[最终用户许可协议|最終使用者協議（EULA）]]，或甚至是在用戶不知情的情況下進行，但它已在iPhone的合約條款中以15,200字訂明，「蘋果公司跟他們的合作伙伴及持牌人可能會收集、使用和分享這些精確的位置數據，包括用戶的蘋果電腦或裝置的實時地理位置<ref name="Guardian">{{Cite news |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/2011/apr/20/iphone-tracking-prompts-privacy-fears |title=iPhone keeps record of everywhere you go |author=Arthur, Charles |date=2011-04-20 |work=The Guardian |accessdate=2011-04-22 |location=UK |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110422011657/http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/2011/apr/20/iphone-tracking-prompts-privacy-fears |archivedate=2011-04-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。」

當iPhone連接電腦同步時，該檔案會自動複製到用戶的電腦。在2011年4月公開發布的一個名為iPhoneTracker的開源碼，能夠把數據轉成一個視覺化的地圖<ref name="GitHub">{{Cite web |title=iPhone Tracker |url=http://petewarden.github.com/iPhoneTracker |accessdate=2011-04-22 |author=Allan, Alasdair |coauthors=Warden, Pete |publisher=[[GitHub|GitHub]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110422095931/http://petewarden.github.com/iPhoneTracker/ |archivedate=2011-04-22 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。該檔案會被加密，如沒有[[越獄_(iOS)|越獄]]手機，將不能刪除<ref name="Time">{{Cite news |url=http://techland.time.com/2011/04/22/how-to-encrypt-your-iphones-location-data-consolidated-db |title=How to Encrypt The Location Data of your iPhone (Consolidated.db) |author=Aamoth, Doug |date=2011-04-22 |work=Time |accessdate=2011-04-22 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110422202515/http://techland.time.com/2011/04/22/how-to-encrypt-your-iphones-location-data-consolidated-db/ |archivedate=2011-04-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

在用戶及[[美联社|美聯社]]以及其他人士提出相關問題後，蘋果公司在2011年4月27日於其網站上作了官方回應<ref name="Apple-location-FAQ">{{Cite press release |url=http://www.apple.com/pr/library/2011/04/27location_qa.html |date=2011-04-27 |accessdate=2011-06-07 |publisher=Apple Inc. |title=Apple Q&A on Location Data |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607035322/http://www.apple.com/pr/library/2011/04/27location_qa.html |archivedate=2011-06-07 }}</ref><ref name="Forbes">{{Cite news |url=http://www.forbes.com/feeds/ap/2011/04/21/technology-technology-hardware-amp-equipment-us-apple-iphone-tracking_8429038.html |title=iPhone, iPad tracking causes alarm |author=Robertson, Jordan |date=2011-04-21 |work=Forbes |accessdate=2011-04-22}}{{dead link|date=August 2011}}</ref>，他們澄清那些資料只是[[WiFi|WiFi]]熱點和手機訊號發射塔發出人群數據來源裡的一小部分，那些都是蘋果公司下載到iPhone的，為了比較GPS進行定位服務更快的效果，因此，那些數據並不代表iPhone的位置。保留數據的容量是一個錯誤。及後蘋果公司發布一個[[IOS版本历史|IOS 4.3.3]]的更新（[[IOS版本历史|IOS 4.2.8]]用於CDMA版iPhone4），用來減少緩衝的容量、停止備份到iTunes，和每當定位服務被停用時把資料完全抹去<ref name="Apple-location-FAQ" />，上傳到蘋果公司的資料可以由用戶從"系統服務"的"手機網絡搜索"中停用。

=== 情報存取 ===
在2013年期間，據報大量監控披露英國及美國的情報機關，分別包括[[美國國家安全局|美國國家安全局（NSA）]]、[[政府通信总部|政府通訊總局（GCHQ）]]曾進入iPhone、[[BlackBerry|BlackBerry]]和[[Android|Android]]手機。當局幾乎能夠讀取所有智能電話的資訊，包括短訊、位置、電郵和筆記<ref name="spiegel20130907">{{Cite news |url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/world/a-920971.html |title=Privacy Scandal: NSA Can Spy on Smart Phone Data |author=Staff |date=2013-09-07 |accessdate=2013-09-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190919033145/https://www.spiegel.de/international/world/privacy-scandal-nsa-can-spy-on-smart-phone-data-a-920971.html |archive-date=2019-09-19 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 限制 ==
{{see also2|{{tsl|en|Hardware restrictions#Apple devices|蘋果公司對硬件產品的限制|蘋果公司對硬件產品的限制}}}}
蘋果公司對iPhone的某些方面作出嚴格的控制，根據{{link-en|Jonathan Zittrain|Jonathan Zittrain}}所述，如iPhone般的{{link-en|專門硬體|Proprietary hardware}}的出現，比早期版本的[[微軟視窗|微軟視窗]]更專門<ref>{{Cite web |title=A Killer Product: Will closed devices like Apple's iPhone murder the Web? |url=http://www.newsweek.com/id/135150 |accessdate=2009-06-16 |date=2008-05-02 |last=Braiker |first=Brian |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090626074049/http://www.newsweek.com/id/135150 |archivedate=2009-06-26 |quote=Through historical accident, we've ended up with a global network that pretty much allows anybody to communicate with anyone else at any time. Devices could be reprogrammed by them at any time, including code written by other people, so you don't have to be a nerd to get the benefits of reprogramming it. [But] this is an historical accident. Now, I see a movement away from that framework—even though it doesn't feel like a movement away. [For example,] an iPhone can only be changed by Steve Jobs or soon, with the software development kit, by programmers that he personally approves that go through his iPhone apps store. Or whimsical applications that run on the Facebook platform or the new Google apps. These are controllable by their vendors in ways that Bill Gates never dreamed of controlling Windows applications. [...] That's the ironic thing. Bill Gates is Mr. Proprietary. But for my purposes, even under the standard Windows operating system from 1990, 1991, you write the code, you can hand it to somebody else and they can run it. Bill Gates has nothing to say about it. So it's funny to think that by moving in Steve Jobs's direction it actually ends up far more proprietary. |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

[[黑客|黑客]]組織已發現許多解決辦法，大部分都是蘋果公司不允許的，並且很難甚至是不能獲得保養服務<ref>{{Cite web |title=Do iPhone Hacks Void Your Warranty? |url=http://www.iphonealley.com/news/do-iphone-hacks-void-your-warranty |accessdate=2009-05-14 |date=2007-10-20 |last=Johnston |first=Michael |publisher=iPhone Alley |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100607043644/http://www.iphonealley.com/news/do-iphone-hacks-void-your-warranty |archivedate=2010-06-07 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。[[iOS越獄|iOS越獄]]讓用戶可以安裝不在[[App_Store_(iOS)|應用程式商店]]下載的應用程式或是修改其基本功能。SIM卡解鎖是容許iPhone於不同電訊商的網絡上使用<ref>{{Cite web |title=iPhone hackers look to an uncertain future |url=http://www.macworld.com/article/132675/2008/03/iphone_sdk_jailbreak.html |accessdate=2009-05-25 |date=2008-05-28 |last=Moren |first=Dan |work=Macworld |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090608184724/http://www.macworld.com/article/132675/2008/03/iphone_sdk_jailbreak.html |archivedate=2009-06-08 |deadurl=no }}</ref>，然而在美國，蘋果公司不可以把保養服務判定無效，除非它顯示出現於售後安裝或安置後或組件故障的問題，例如未經授權的應用程式，受到[[聯邦貿易委員會|聯邦貿易委員會]]的{{link-en|1975年的馬格納森-莫斯保養法|Magnuson-Moss Warranty Act of 1975}}監管<ref>[http://eshop.macsales.com/Search/displayFAQDetails.cfm?ID=656 FAQ Details] {{Wayback|url=http://eshop.macsales.com/Search/displayFAQDetails.cfm?ID=656 |date=20130718095945 }}. Eshop.macsales.com（March 27, 2013）. Retrieved on July 30, 2013.</ref>。

iPhone還備有區域和設定，能讓家長設置限制下載的應用程式，或是對使用中的應用程式作出控制和限制<ref>{{Cite web |title=set restrictions |url=http://www.imore.com/iphone-101-set-parental-controls-iphone |accessdate=2012-10-25 |date=2009-04-13 |publisher=Imore.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121028134150/http://www.imore.com/iphone-101-set-parental-controls-iphone |archivedate=2012-10-28 |deadurl=no }}</ref>，而這些限制是需要密碼的輸入<ref name="restrictions">{{Cite web |title=IOS Understanding Restrictions |url=http://support.apple.com/kb/ht4213 |accessdate=2012-09-26 |work=Apple Inc. |publisher=Apple Inc. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121002071112/http://support.apple.com/kb/HT4213 |archivedate=2012-10-02 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

=== 啓動 ===
iPhone一般會阻擋其他媒體播放器和網絡功能，除非是受到認可電訊商的授權。在2007年7月3日，[[挪威|挪威]]程式員[[约恩·莱克·约翰森|Jon Lech Johansen]]在他的博客上指，他已成功繞過這個要求並破解iPhone的其他功能及結合其他自訂應用程式及修改[[iTunes|iTunes]]的二進制程式，並發布軟件供其他人使用<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://nanocr.eu/2007/07/03/iphone-without-att/ |title=iPhone Independence Day |last=Johansen |first=Jon Lech |date=2007-07-03 |publisher=nanocr.eu |authorlink=Jon Lech Johansen |accessdate=2008-06-06 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080602133134/http://nanocr.eu/2007/07/03/iphone-without-att/ |archivedate=2008-06-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[英國|英國]]的[[O2_(英國)|O2]]網絡，可以讓用戶在網上購買早期版本的iPhone並利用iTunes來把它啓動<ref>{{Cite web |title=iPhone 3G |url=http://store.apple.com/uk/browse/home/shop_iphone/family/iphone |accessdate=2009-05-14 |publisher=Apple Store (UK) |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090604212451/http://store.apple.com/uk/browse/home/shop_iphone/family/iphone |archivedate=2009-06-04 |deadurl=no }}</ref>，即使不需要，廠商通常會為買家方便而提供啓動服務；在[[美國|美國]]，蘋果公司已開始為購買iPhone3G和iPhone 3GS買家提供免費送貨服務，改变设备須於店內啓動的方式。[[百思买|百思买]]及[[沃爾瑪|沃爾瑪]]也將會出售iPhone<ref name="Buy iPhone">{{Cite web |title=Apple —iPhone —Buy iPhone 3G |url=http://www.apple.com/iphone/buy/ |accessdate=2009-06-14 |publisher=Apple Inc. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090627163700/http://www.apple.com/iphone/buy/ |archivedate=2009-06-27 |deadurl=no }}{{verify source|date=April 2012}}</ref>。

